Churchville Downs has banned the use of selfie sticks . 
  The Louisville track hosts the annual Kentucky Derby on May 2 . 
  It joins a growing list of museums, music festivals and sports venues that have banned the devices . 
  A spokesman for Churchill Downs said that the ban was designed to protect horses and spectators . 
  Other events such as the Coachella and Lollapalooza music festivals have also banned the poles . 
 